messages.content:
Based on the search results, here's a comparison of the car rental prices at Hollywood Burbank Airport for the two different pickup dates:

## **Pickup Date: November 17th, 2024 (Day after tomorrow)**

**Best Available Rates:**
- **Economy (Hyundai Veloster)**: **$47.74/day**
- **Compact (Nissan Versa)**: **$49.83/day**
- **Intermediate (Toyota Corolla)**: **$50.97/day**
- **SUV (Nissan Rogue)**: **$66.31/day**

## **Pickup Date: November 18th, 2024 (Two days after tomorrow)**

**Best Available Rates:**
- **Economy (Hyundai Veloster)**: **$43.27/day**
- **Compact (Nissan Versa)**: **$44.20/day**
- **Intermediate (Toyota Corolla)**: **$48.22/day**

## **Price Difference Summary**

**Savings by waiting one extra day:**
- **Economy car**: Save **$4.47** ($47.74 → $43.27)
- **Compact car**: Save **$5.63** ($49.83 → $44.20)
- **Intermediate car**: Save **$2.75** ($50.97 → $48.22)

**Conclusion**: You'll save approximately **$2.75-$5.63** by renting the car on November 18th instead of November 17th. The savings are modest but consistent across all car categories, with compact cars offering the biggest discount.

supplier_info.dropoff_instructions:
After collecting your luggage, please call our phone number to arrange your shuttle pick-up on on 07 3006 7442 and International Dialling: +61 7 3006 7442. If you are unable to reach us by phone, proceed directly to the shuttle pick-up point. 

For International Bookings: From the arrivals hall, turn left and walk past the Coffee Club. Continue straight ahead towards the exit doors located in the far corner of the terminal. Exit the terminal and head down the ramp to your left, following the pathway to the end of the covered walkway. Cross the pedestrian crossing and wait at shuttle bay 3/4 for the Goldcar shuttle. 

For Domestic Bookings: From the baggage claim area, exit the terminal through the main doors. Walk towards the skywalk and proceed up the travelator. At the top of the travelator, turn left and walk across the skywalk to the second travelator on your right. Exit the terminal, walk across the Skywalk and go down the travelator to B1/B2 on the ground floor. Please wait here for the Goldcar shuttle to collect you.

### **Option 1: Pickup November 22nd at 10:00 AM**

- **Most Common Price Range**: $39.83 - $51.99 USD
- **Sample Options**:
  - MG 3 Compact: $39.83 USD

If you need a larger car, the Compact (Suzuki Baleno/Hyundai i30) is only ~ $2–3 more per day on either date.

reviews.negative: Insurance costs were outrageous.
reviews.positive: Nice car, service was good.

reviews.negative:
My reservation was for Volkswagen Tiguan. 
The definition of this car category was:  MID size SUV with a capacity for 3 Large bags. 
Europcar gave me Cupra Formentor which is by any standard a small SUV or not an SUV at all.
If you look at the range of Cupra/Seat, the Ateca is the equivalent in size (mid SUV) and the Formentor is below it. 
Furthermore, There is absolutely no room for  3 Large bags (as reserved) in the Formentor.
I have pictures to support this.
Europcar were willing to change the car to station wagon to solve the 3 Large bags mismatch 
but this was not SUV and because I have a back problem, I need the SUV height.
They said they have no other SUV for me. 
So after a long flight I had no strength to continue to argue with them and I took the Formentor.
We had 3 Large bags so we drive with one of them in the cabin for 17 days!

Here is the complete information your friend needs for her car rental from Vienna International Airport to Salzburg:

## **Supplier Details**
- **Company**: Megadrive
- **Rating**: 8.4/10 (Very Good) based on 2,520 reviews
- **Location**: Vienna International Airport, Flughafen Wien-Schwechat, Parkhaus 4, Wien, Austria, 1300
- **Pickup Instructions**: Exit baggage claim, turn left, walk through pedestrian tunnel to Car park 4 (P4), desk on level 0
- **Opening Hours**: 
  - Pickup: 8:00 AM - 4:00 PM (Dec 10)
  - Drop-off: 24/7 (Dec 15)

## **Customer Reviews Summary**
**Positive feedback**:
- Professional staff at counter
- Easy drop-off process
- Quick and efficient service
- Clean vehicles
- Exact car as booked

**Areas of concern**:
- Some waiting time at pickup (30+ minutes reported)
- Directions could be clearer
- One customer reported not receiving the car (rare case)

## **Vehicle Details**
- **Car**: Volkswagen Polo (Economy class)
- **Features**: 4-door, 4-seater, manual transmission, air conditioning, unlimited mileage
- **Fuel Policy**: Like for like
- **Price**: $298.13 USD for 6 days

## **Insurance Packages**
**Full Protection Insurance**:
- **Price**: $103.23 USD (includes all taxes and fees)
- **Coverage includes**:
  - Damage excess protection (up to $1,616.25)
  - Theft protection (up to $1,616.25)
  - Windows, mirrors, wheels & tyres
  - Key loss & roadside assistance
  - Free cancellation

The standard rental includes basic CDW (Collision Damage Waiver) and Theft Protection, but with significant excess amounts. The Full Protection package eliminates these excess charges and provides comprehensive coverage for all potential issues.

- **Rating:** 7.5/10 (Good) based on 220 reviews
- **Operating Hours:** 8:00 AM - 10:00 PM (pickup), 24/7 (drop-off in Lyon)

## **Pricing**
- **Base Rental Price:** $374.17 USD
- **One-way Fee:** €60 EUR
- **Total Drive-away Price:** ~$440.93 USD

## **Insurance & Protection Packages**

**Full Protection Insurance:** $111.24 USD
- **Coverage includes:**
  - Damage excess protection (covers up to $2,781.63 excess)
  - Theft protection (covers up to $2,781.63 excess)
  - Protection for windows, mirrors, wheels, and tires
  - Key loss and roadside assistance coverage
  - Free cancellation

## **Customer Reviews Summary**

**Recent feedback highlights:**
- **Positive:** Clean cars, easy drop-off process, good vehicle condition
- **Negative:** Long wait times at pickup (up to 2 hours), occasional vehicle substitutions, booking location changes

**Rating Breakdown:**
- Overall value: 7.4/10
- Helpfulness: 7.6/10
- Pick-up speed: 6.0/10 (needs improvement)
- Drop-off speed: 8.5/10
- Car cleanliness: 8.0/10

## **Important Notes**
- **Deposit required:** €500 EUR
- **Damage excess:** €2,500 EUR (without Full Protection)
- **Theft excess:** €2,500 EUR (without Full Protection)
- **Free cancellation** available on both rental and insurance

The Full Protection insurance at $111.24 seems reasonably priced given the high excess amounts, and it provides comprehensive coverage including roadside assistance. However, your friend should be prepared for potential wait times at pickup at CDG Airport.

**October 10th (tomorrow) at 8 PM**: 85 vehicles available
**October 11th (day after tomorrow) at 8 PM**: 85 vehicles available

Both searches show excellent availability with pickup at 8 PM and return at 8 PM on October 17th at the same location.

messages.content:
Based on my search, here's what I found for your car rental needs at Miami International Airport:

## **Car Availability Summary**

✅ **December 1st, 2024 (6 PM)**: **92 vehicles available**  
❌ **December 2nd, 2024 (6 PM)**: **No vehicles available**

**Recommendation**: Book for **December 1st at 6 PM** to secure your rental.

## **Top Non-Sixt Rental Options (December 1st-8th)**

### **1. Dollar - Ford Mustang Convertible**
- **Price**: $690.53 for 7 days
- **Rating**: 8.2/10 (Very Good) - 7,729 reviews
- **Vehicle**: 4-seater convertible, automatic transmission
- **Features**: Free cancellation, unlimited mileage, free fuel tank

### **2. Avis - Chevrolet Cruze**
- **Price**: $361.65 for 7 days ⭐ **Best Value**
- **Rating**: 8.3/10 (Very Good) - 2,775 reviews
- **Vehicle**: 5-seater intermediate car, automatic transmission
- **Features**: Free cancellation, unlimited mileage

## **Supplier Reviews (Non-Sixt)**

### **Dollar Reviews Summary**:
- **Overall Rating**: 8.2/10 from 7,729 reviews
- **Strengths**: Excellent drop-off speed (8.9/10), good car cleanliness (8.2/10)
- **Common Feedback**: 
  - Generally good value for money
  - Some wait times at pickup counter during peak hours
  - Helpful staff but occasionally understaffed

### **Avis Reviews Summary**:
- **Overall Rating**: 8.3/10 from 2,775 reviews
- **Strengths**: Excellent drop-off speed (9.3/10), good customer service
- **Common Feedback**:
  - Fast service overall
  - Some vehicles may have minor maintenance issues (tire pressure warnings)
  - Occasional unexpected charges reported

## **Booking Recommendation**
Given the availability and your requirements, I recommend booking the **Avis Chevrolet Cruze** for **December 1st at 6 PM** as it offers the best value at $361.65 for the week while maintaining good ratings. The Dollar Mustang Convertible is also an excellent option if you prefer a more premium experience.

Based on my search, here's what I found for your car rental needs at John F. Kennedy International Airport:

## **Car Availability Summary**

✅ **Good news!** There are **139 cars available** for pickup at 5 PM tomorrow (November 20th) and **126 cars available** for pickup at 5 PM the day after (November 21st), with return on November 27th at 5 PM.

## **Available Suppliers (Excluding Avis)**

The main suppliers with available vehicles are:

1. **Dollar** - 58 vehicles available
2. **Budget** - 40 vehicles available  
3. **Sixt** - 27 vehicles available

## **Dollar Supplier Reviews** (Most Available Options)

**Overall Rating: 6.3/10 (OK)** based on 711 reviews

**Customer Feedback Highlights:**
- **Positive:** Easy drop-off process (8.0/10), generally clean vehicles (7.1/10)
- **Concerns:** 
  - Slow pickup times (5.6/10)
  - Mixed experiences with customer service
  - Some customers reported agencies being closed upon arrival
  - Security deposit amounts can be high (up to 10x rental cost)

**Recent Reviews:**
- "Easy to process" - Couple traveler (8.6/10)
- "They closed before I landed and I couldn't get my car" - Family traveler (2.0/10)
- "Overall ease to get and drop off car was great" - Family traveler (8.3/10)

## **Price Range**
- **Economy cars:** Starting around $425-449 for the week
- **Intermediate cars:** Around $562-680 for the week
- **Full-size vehicles:** Around $764+ for the week

All vehicles come with automatic transmission, unlimited mileage, and free cancellation. The pickup location is at the JFK car rental center with shuttle service available.

messages.content:
Based on my search, I have good news for your business trip to Washington! Here's what I found:

## Car Rental Availability ✅

**Both dates have excellent availability** at Seattle-Tacoma International Airport:

- **November 25th, 2024 at 3:00 PM**: 75 vehicles available
- **November 26th, 2024 at 3:00 PM**: 75 vehicles available

Both options return on December 2nd at 3:00 PM to the same location.

## Supplier Reviews (Excluding Hertz)

Here are the reviews for other major suppliers:

### **Budget** - 7.1/10 (Good) - 698 reviews
**Strengths:**
- Drop-off speed: 9.6/10 (Excellent)
- Car cleanliness: 8.1/10 (Very Good)
- Location convenience: 8.3/10

**Common Concerns:**
- Long wait times at pickup (up to 2-3 hours reported)
- Some unexpected additional charges
- Limited staff during peak times

**Recent Review Summary:** "Clean cars but be prepared for long queues at pickup. The drop-off process is very efficient."

### **Avis** - 7.3/10 (Good) - 263 reviews
**Strengths:**
- Drop-off speed: 9.4/10 (Excellent)
- Car condition: 8.2/10 (Very Good)
- Overall value: 7.6/10

**Common Concerns:**
- Pickup speed: 4.5/10 (Slow)
- Some customers received different vehicles than booked
- Navigation systems not always included

**Recent Review Summary:** "Good cars and smooth drop-off, but pickup can be slow. Staff are generally helpful once you reach them."

## Recommendation
Both **Budget** and **Avis** have solid ratings and are reliable alternatives to Hertz. Budget has more reviews (698 vs 263), while Avis has slightly better overall ratings. I'd recommend **Avis** for slightly better service quality, or **Budget** if you prefer a company with more extensive experience at this location.

reviews.positive: It was very fortunate that I was given a bigger car than I had originally booked as the boot space was essential for our trip.
The customer service was impeccable, before and after collection/drop-off off the car.  The Avis representative game me an upgrade to European SUV and I couldn't have been more happier.
reviews.negative: Avis office, indeed car rental offices in general at Canberra airport, was not in the terminal and not the easiest to find.

reviews.positive: Upgraded several classes due to lack of availability!
reviews.negative: The car had a flat on pick-up

The car, a VW T-cross, had around 27,000km on the clock and the performance was less than expected. This could also have been the result of previous renters using 91 octane fuel instead of the 95 octane recommended by the manufacturers. The instrument data continually showed the left rear tyre below pressure despite being inflated to the required pressure by me and the NRMA. This was an unecessary worry.
reviews.positive: The seamless booking and ease of pick-up/drop off.
Speedy service, helpful staff, easy location, great economical car.
reviews.negative: No complaints!

Here is the detailed information for your rental car and supplier:

### **Vehicle Details**
- **Make & Model**: Toyota Corolla (Compact)
- **Transmission**: Automatic
- **Seats**: 5
- **Doors**: 4
- **Air Conditioning**: Yes
- **Mileage**: Unlimited kilometers
- **Fuel Policy**: Like-for-like (return with the same level as received)
- **Luggage Space**: 1 large suitcase + 1 small suitcase
- **Free Cancellation**: Up to 48 hours before pick-up

### **Supplier Details**
- **Company**: Avis
- **Rating**: 9.1/10 ("Superb") based on 273 reviews
- **Pick-up Location**: Canberra Airport (CBR) – In Terminal
- **Drop-off Location**: Adelaide Airport (ADL) – In Terminal
- **Operating Hours**: 24/7 at both locations

### **Pricing & Fees**
- **Total Rental Cost**: **US$847.41** (approx. 3-day rental)
- **Security Deposit**: **US$328.43** (AUD 500)
- **Damage Excess**: **US$3,576.55** (AUD 5,445)
- **Theft Excess**: **US$3,576.55** (AUD 5,445)
- **One-Way Fee**: **Included** (no extra charge for Canberra → Adelaide drop-off)

### **Included in Rental**
- Collision Damage Waiver (CDW)
- Theft Protection
- Third-Party Liability (TPL)
- Free amendments

### **Optional Add-ons**
- **Full Protection Insurance**: US$117.50 (covers damage/theft excess)
- **Additional Driver**: US$14.91 per rental
- **Baby Seat**: US$52.80 per rental
- **Booster Seat**: US$59.67 per rental

### **Customer Reviews Highlights**
- **Pros**: Fast service, helpful staff, easy pick-up/drop-off, free upgrades.
- **Cons**: Some cars had minor issues (e.g., tire pressure warnings), and the rental desk at Canberra Airport can be slightly hard to locate.

### **Important Notes**
- **Payment**: A credit or debit card in the main driver’s name is required at pick-up.
- **Fuel**: Return the car with the same fuel level to avoid charges.

Here is the detailed information for your rental:

Vehicle Details
• Make & Model: Mazda CX-5 (Standard class)  
• Transmission: Automatic  
• Seats: 5  
• Doors: 4  
• Air-conditioning: Yes  
• Luggage: 2 large + 1 small suitcase  
• Fuel policy: Like-for-like (return with same level)  
• Mileage: Unlimited kilometres  

Supplier Details
• Company: Ace Rental Cars  
• Rating: 8.9 / 10 (“Fabulous”) – based on 1,612 reviews  
• Pick-up location: 17 Ross Drive, Perth Airport, WA 6105 (Shuttle-bus service)  
• Drop-off location: 330 Nudgee Road, Brisbane Airport, QLD 4011 (Shuttle-bus service)  

Pick-up Instructions
After collecting your luggage at Perth Airport, call 1800 620 408 (or +61 8 9479 5016) to request the free Ace shuttle.  
• T1 Virgin – exit the main doors and wait by the T1 domestic sign.  
• T1 International – exit the main doors and wait at bus stand L.  
• T3 & T4 – exit outside and wait in the centre lane next to the rideshare sign.  
The last shuttle leaves 30 minutes before the counter closes.

Opening Hours
• Perth Airport counter: 09:00 – 17:00 (26 Oct)  
• Brisbane Airport counter: 07:00 – 17:00 (28 Oct)

Pricing Snapshot
• 3-day rental (26–28 Oct): ≈ US$269.59 (pay now)  
• One-way fee: included (≈ US$1,327)  
• Security deposit: US$270 (≈ AUD 100)  
• Damage excess: ≈ AUD 5,900 (≈ US$3,914) – can be reduced with optional Full-Protection insurance.

Included Cover
• Collision Damage Waiver (CDW)  
• Theft Cover  
• Third-Party Liability (TPL)

Optional Extras
• Additional driver: ≈ US$10 per rental  
• Baby seat (0–9 kg): ≈ US$12 per rental  
• Booster seat (18–45 kg): ≈ US$12 per rental

You can add Full-Protection insurance for about US$110 to eliminate the damage-excess liability and gain free cancellation.

   • Pick-up Counter: 3150 S 160th St, Suite 510, Seattle, WA 98158  
     – Access via free shuttle bus from SEA baggage-claim level 3  
   • Drop-off Counter: 7000 NE Airport Way, Portland, OR 97218  
     – Located inside PDX Car Rental Centre (connected to terminal)

3. Rental Period  
   • Pick-up: Sun 1 Dec 2024 – 11:00 AM  
   • Drop-off: Sat 7 Dec 2024 – 5:00 PM  
   • Duration: 7 days

4. Pricing (USD)

   • One-way fee (pay at counter):  $98.25

messages.content:
Here are the details for your friends' self-driving trip in Austria from March 15th to 22nd, 2025:

### **Vehicle Details**
- **Model**: Skoda Scala (Compact car)
- **Transmission**: Manual
- **Seats**: 5
- **Doors**: 4
- **Luggage**: 1 small suitcase, 1 large suitcase
- **Fuel Policy**: Like for like (return with the same fuel level)
- **Mileage**: Unlimited
- **Air Conditioning**: Yes
- **Free Cancellation**: Up to 48 hours before pick-up

### **Supplier Ratings (Europcar)**
- **Overall Rating**: 8.2/10 (Very Good) based on 1,723 reviews
- **Breakdown**:
  - **Car Cleanliness**: 8.9/10
  - **Drop-off Speed**: 8.8/10
  - **Helpfulness**: 8.4/10
  - **Overall Value for Money**: 7.5/10
  - **Pick-up Speed**: 7.2/10

### **User Comments (Recent Reviews)**
- **Positive Feedback**:
  - "Great car, great fit for a family. A lot of space." (9.4/10)
  - Generally praised for cleanliness and helpful staff.

- **Common Complaints**:
  - **Car Availability Issues**: Some customers reported not receiving the booked car type (e.g., manual vs. automatic).
  - **Pick-up Delays**: Slow pick-up process, especially at busy times.
  - **Minor Scratches**: Disputes over pre-existing minor damages noted during drop-off.
  - **Late Arrivals**: If flights are delayed, the rental desk may close (e.g., one group arrived at 23:10 but the desk closed at 23:00, causing a 24-hour delay).

### **Pricing & Fees**
- **Total Cost**: ~$451.49 USD (8-day rental)
- **One-Way Fee**: $28.94 USD (Vienna to Graz)
- **Security Deposit**: ~$946 USD (refundable)
- **Damage Excess**: ~$1,302 USD (covered if Full Protection is purchased)

### **Pick-up & Drop-off Locations**
- **Pick-up**: Vienna International Airport (Car Rental Centre, Level 0 of Parkhaus 4)
- **Drop-off**: Graz Airport (In-terminal counter)

### **Recommendations**
- **Book Early**: Ensure availability of manual transmission if preferred.
- **Check Flight Delays**: Confirm desk hours to avoid late pick-up issues.
- **Inspect Car Thoroughly**: Document any pre-existing damage to avoid disputes.
- **Consider Full Protection**: Reduces liability for damages (adds ~$141 USD).

Your friends should have a smooth trip with Europcar, but they should double-check their booking details and arrive early for pick-up to avoid delays.

reviews.negative:
The verbal FREE upgrade offered by agent Sybille, (due to a last-minute cancellation) was subsequently amended to a "choice upgrade' at an extra cost of CHF 74.28/day (x12 days), i.e. CHF 891.36 more than agreed through you. (that's C$1,488.57, i.e. 367% more than the basic rental prepaid through rentalcars.com!!! (that excessive rental cost noted above is exclusive of the 8.10% VAT, and the "Premium Location Fee" of 20%, which was not noted on the rentalcars.com agreement.  - not holding it against you....but SixT certainly lives up to its worldwide reputation as untrust-worthy rental company.
When they emailed me a request to rate their service, I told them loud and clear that unless they amend the final charge upon return of the vehicle, I'll see them in court.
The credit-card pre-authorization (Security Deposit) of CHF 1,463.56 was cancelled/withdrawn two days before end of rental, but to this day, I don't know what they debited to my credit-card, as there is still no Sixt debit showing on my Visa account.
That said, I had also purchased a CDW through rentalcoverage.com, the confirmation of which I showed to the SixT agent upon pickup (she did not take the details), but upon return of the vehicle they claimed that I damaged the rear-left wheel rim (5-10 cms down to primer); when I told the receiving agent that I a) have CDW coverage and b) had taken photos at time of pickup, which clearly shows the pre-existing damage, she noted it on the Return-Receipt, but I am now being hounded by the SixT-Damage dept. (As I'm still travelling, I have had no time to respond, and frankly see no reason why I should respond to that department.
Last, but not least, Sixt's Diamond member should not be permitted to push through a line of 12 people waiting to be served, when there is no dedicated Diamond-Member counter.
Decency toward the common-mortals is sorely lacking at Sixt!
PS: I've rented cars through rentalcars.com previously and everything went without a hitch....s
reviews.positive:
Originally, I appreciated the offer of a FREE upgrade to a BMW x2, however that pleasure was short-lived (see 'what you didn't like').
This slightly larger vehicle was good to drive, but had useless gadgets which made driving in darkness outright dangerous. I did like the automatic transmission and the heads-up display, though. The fuel-mileage was great too.
The SIXT rental desk is easily located and car condition is good
reviews.negative: The SIXT representative keen to push me to upgrade my car (which required CHF 50 per day) and insurance.  After my rejection, I was  told to wait 30min as my booked needed more time to do cleaning.  I booked the car at 2pm; I finally got the car (same size/group; but not my )

The cost of additional full protection of insurance is quite high
